		<div id="comment_body_64569491"><p>Higher demand does attract new investment, and that can be good for renewables.  The main costs of solar power and wind are capital costs,  and a huge new source of demand can attract investment to bring new renewable and grid storage projects online.</p><p>The problem with that rosy scenario is this: the industry is in a break-neck race to achieve dominance in a rapidly emerging and purportedly ultra-lucrative field.  You could build your datacenter around a renewable energy project that would cut your electricit<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64569491">

</div>
</div>

